    <abstract>
      <t>In-situ Operations, Administration, and Maintenance (IOAM) is used for recording and collecting operational and telemetry information while the packet traverses a path between two points in the network. This document defines how IOAM data fields are transported with MPLS data plane encapsulation using MPLS Network Action (MNA) and follows the MNA framework defined in draft-ietf-mpls-mna-fwk.</t>
    </abstract>
